The paper deals with collaborative exploration of graphs, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The use of communication and the analysis of competitive ratios suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the tight bounds on the number of agents needed for exploration suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
